               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-96-person1057">
                  ROBERT 
                  BRIDGES
               <interp inst="t18270913-96-person1057" type="surname" value="BRIDGES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-96-person1057" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-96-person1057" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I met the prisoner in the Hay-market, on the 31st of July, and she took me to a house in <placeName id="t18270913-96-crimeloc557">Bennett-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-96-crimeloc557" type="placeName" value="Bennett-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-96-crimeloc557" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-96-off555 t18270913-96-crimeloc557"></join>; we slept together, and in the morning I missed these things off the floor; she was still there - I do not know that she had left the room; my clothes were still on the ground; I asked her about it; she said if I did not hold my tongue, she would get somebody to throw me out of the window, and that I should find them when I got a light - I have not found them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not tell your friends that you had been robbed by three men in the street? A. I did so because I did not like to tell the truth - I was sober - the door was fastened inside.</p>
